Joint New Editorial Supported Abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- The joint New Year editorial of the newspapers of the Workers' Party of Korea, the Korean People's Army and the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League of the DPRK is supported in different countries.
 The National Council of the Lebanese Communist Party in a statement on Jan. 13 said that the DPRK has achieved brilliant victory in the struggle to defend the sovereignty of the country under the leadership of the Workers' Party of Korea and instilled great strength and courage into the world peace-loving people last year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the WPK set forth militant tasks to be fulfilled by the Korean people this year to achieve great victory on the three fronts of politics and ideology, anti-imperialism and military affairs and economy and science and attain the reunification of the country and peace on the Korean peninsula, the statement reiterated the council's solidarity with the Korean people in their struggle to achieve the reunification of the country and peace on the Korean peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Genaro Ledesma Izquieta, chairman of the People's Front of Workers, Peasants and Students of Peru, issued a statement titled "We extend full support to the reunification of Korea" on Jan. 11. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that the slogan "Let us pave a wide avenue for independent reunification through national cooperation under the banner of our nation-first spirit!" set forth in the joint New Year editorial is the one all the Koreans in the north and the south and overseas should hold aloft with firm faith and optimism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the cause of national reunification, the greatest desire of the Korean people, is undergoing a severe test due to the U.S. military moves, the statement stressed that a widespread movement should be waged for the reunification of Korea worldwide.

Implementation of Appeal Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- An Kyong Ho, chairman of the North Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification (Pomminryon), in a statement on Jan. 24 said that the North Headquarters of Pomminryon would always take the lead in the struggle to smash the U.S. imperialists' every war move and achieve the country's independent reunification under the uplifted banner of the Korean nation-first spirit.
 Expressing his strong support to the appeal made by the joint meeting of the government, political parties and organizations of the DPRK to all Koreans to turn out as one in the anti-U.S., anti-war struggle, he underscored the need to take practical actions to build the Korean nation's confrontation with the U.S. in order to decisively frustrate the U.S. moves for a nuclear war and defend the sovereignty of the country and the nation and peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the Songun politics is patriotic politics for defending the Korean nation, as it is aimed to protect its well-being and peace, he called on the 70 million Koreans to firmly support and defend the Songun politics which helps avert a nuclear holocaust on the Korean peninsula and guarantee lasting peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed belief that all the reunification movement organizations in the south and overseas supporting the June 15 joint declaration would positively respond to the appeal of the joint meeting for waging a vigorous anti-U.S., anti-war struggle to defend the dignity and destiny of the Korean nation.

Rodong Sinmun on Songun Politics 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- The Songun politics of the Workers' Party of Korea is the invincible politics whose validity has been proved amid the stern test of history and an all-powerful treasured sword for winning a victory in the revolution, says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article.
 The WPK's Songun politics is the most effective political mode as it most correctly reflects the aspiration and demand of the popular masses who value independence and helps successfully realize them in the present times, the article notes, and continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This politics is the most just politics reflecting the demand of the prevailing situation and will of the popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics is the most popular politics as it is aimed to defend independence of the popular masses and serve the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This politics is based on the philosophy of arms that the army represents the Party, the State and the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attaching great importance to the military affairs in the socialist society is the most just measure to protect the destiny of the people and guarantee their life. No political mode is, therefore, as efficient as the Songun politics enforced by the WPK and the socialist regime which struggle for the independent and creative life of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people live and struggle with the faith that they can live without sweets but not without bullets. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This clearly proves that the WPK's Songun politics is one for the people and an efficient political mode absolutely supported by the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics is the invincible politics guaranteeing the sovereignty and dignity of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Sovereignty is the life and soul of the country and the nation and socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Sovereignty is unthinkable without an army in the present world where the imperialists' military high-handed and arbitrary practices are rampant. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An invincible army is the source of extraordinary pluck, strong national self-respect and dignified and independent diplomacy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics based on the invincible revolutionary armed forces is the principled and just anti-imperialist independent politics, noble patriotic politics reliably defending the demand for independence of the popular masses and their interests and sovereignty and dignity of the country and the nation from all forms of infringement of the imperialist reactionaries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics firmly guarantees independence of the DPRK and helps the socialist motherland fully demonstrate its dignity, honor and might as a bulwark of independence.

Five-thousand-year-long History of Nation, Pride of Korean People 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- The Korean people are a proud nation that has a time-honored history and excellent traditions with which to exalt the Korean nation-first spirit, says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people are a proud nation that has made a long history and brilliant culture, living in the same territory as a homogeneous nation from ancient times. The history of the Korean nation with Tangun with as its ancestral father is spanning more than five thousand years. Tangun, the founder-father of Korea, chose the then Walled City of Pyongyang (Pyongyang at present) as a capital and declared the birth of the country and named it "Korea." With the foundation of Tangun Korea the Koreans were the first to usher in the era of the state and civilization in the East. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The five-thousand-year-long history of the Korean nation can be described as a history of struggle during which it has courageously fought against foreign aggressors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The foreign aggressors had incessantly invaded Korea up to date from ancient times. Whenever the aggressors committed invasion, however, the Koreans turned out as one in a sacred fight to defend the country from the invasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The aggressors failed to break patriotism and bravery of the Koreans and bring them to their knees. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The five-thousand-year-long history of the Korean nation can also be termed a proud history of creation in which it brought into full bloom and developed the brilliant culture of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people are a resourceful and civilized nation that has brought into full bloom the culture of the East and made great contributions to the development of culture of humankind from ancient times. They have created numerous excellent wealths in science, technology, literature and arts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today in the DPRK the advantageous national character of the Korean nation has been carried forward and developed on a high level under the wise guidance of Kim Jong Il, the incarnation of patriotism. The traditions and customs of the Korean nation have been preserved and developed in all aspects of social life and the spirit and soul of the nation are prevalent in literary and art works, edifices, the dressing up and etiquette. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is only too natural for all the Koreans to be proud of their history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No force on earth can be a match for the concerted efforts of the 70 million Koreans who get united with the pride and confidence in the advantages of the nation.

Anniversary of North Headquarters of Pomminryon Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- Minju Joson today dedicates an article to the 13th anniversary of the North Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification (Jan. 25, 1991).
 It was an epochal occasion in powerfully promoting the movement for national reunification relying on the driving force of the Korean nation, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the last more than a decade since its formation the headquarters has played a vanguard role in the struggle to achieve independent reunification through national cooperation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Serious obstacles are lying in the way of the movement for the nation and independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists announced a new plan to bolster up the U.S. troops in south Korea and a new war scenario to invade the DPRK and have staged ceaseless war exercises targeted against the north, deteriorating the situation. Pro-U.S. sycophantic and traitorous forces in south Korea are throwing hurdles in the way of the process of improving the inter-Korean relations and achieving the cause of reunification by zealously supporting the U.S. in its vicious moves against the north and reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such moves of the U.S. and the south Korean pro-U.S. flunkeyists against the north and reunification are stumbling blocks in the way of national unity and independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation should frustrate the war moves of the U.S. imperialists and the south Korean bellicose elements against the north and pave the way for peace and peaceful reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historic June 15 joint declaration is a great programme for national reunification as it reflects the desire of all the Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pomminryon should thoroughly reject even the slightest intention to violate the basic spirit of the joint declaration and powerfully encourage all Koreans to implement it and thus give fuller play to its vitality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pomminryon's patriotic cause of reunification is bound to triumph as long as there are the great Songun policy, the will of the Korean nation to achieve the cause of independent reunification of the country and the June 15 joint declaration, a milestone of national unity and reunification.

Rodong Sinmun on Confrontation with Imperialists 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 25 (KCNA) -- The confrontation with imperialists is a military confrontation and, at the same time, a confrontation between the Koreans and imperialists in faith and will, says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article. It goes on:
 Any people strong in revolutionary faith and will and countries which resolutely struggle against the imperialists with a principled stand are sure to emerge victorious. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Bush bellicose forces invaded Afghanistan under the pretext of eradicating the "kingpin of terrorism", "den of terrorists" and then provoked the Iraqi war to overthrow Saddam's regime. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In those wars the U.S. applied every most sinister and cunning method including destructive warfare, horror warfare and psychological warfare. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Weak in the revolutionary faith and will and unaware of the enemy's invasion, the Iraqi army and people were deceived by the U.S. propaganda. They did such folly as harbouring an illusion about aggressors and welcoming them as "liberators." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Whoever lacks faith and will would meet the same tragic destiny as Iraq did in the confrontation with the imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sovereignty of the country and the destiny of the people are guaranteed by the revolutionary faith and will. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and people of the DPRK possess the most transparent revolutionary faith and will. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They do not fear the U.S. high-handed practices but are courageously standing against them with faith in the victory and strong pluck. They are reacting to the U.S. hard line policy with the toughest stand with the firm faith and strong pluck that they will surely emerge victorious in the confrontation with the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary faith, gut and pluck of the army and people of the DPRK are the source of their inexhaustible strength and an important guarantee for their victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No force on earth can defeat the people ready to die. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is the basis of the revolutionary faith and will of the army and people of the DPRK who value independence as their life and soul. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Having this revolutionary faith and will they will surely win ultimate victory in the confrontation with the U.S. and build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation of Juche on this land.

Story Firing Range Project Denounced in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 24 (KCNA) -- The Headquarters of the Movement for Eradicating GIs' Crimes in South Korea, the People for Achieving Peace and Reunification, the Green Federation and other organizations of south Korea reportedly called a press conference denouncing the illegal expansion project of U.S. troops' firing range in Jangpha-ri, Phaphyong-myon, Phaju City, Kyonggi Province, on Jan. 19.
 The press conference was held to condemn the U.S. troops in south Korea for driving iron pillars for iron entanglements into the ground around the expansion project of the Story firing range after starting it on Jan. 15. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the press conference speakers said that the project is aimed to destroy the environment, wreck peace and create tension. They stressed the need to wage a dynamical struggle to check the project together with the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants in a press release strongly demanded an immediate stop to the project and the closure of the firing range, saying that the U.S. troops' project is an act of ignoring our sovereignty.

U.S. Urged to Drop Its Hostile Policy towards DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 24 (KCNA) -- Whether the DPRK-U.S. hostile relations are terminated and a war is averted on the Korean peninsula or not entirely depends on whether the United States drops its hostile policy to stifle the DPRK or not. If the U.S. sincerely wishes to solve the nuclear issue between the DPRK and the U.S. and put an end to the relations of confrontation between the two countries, the former should take a practical and bold action to roll back its hostile policy to stifle the latter. Rodong Sinmun today says this in a signed article. It continues:
 The present DPRK-U.S. relations present themselves as a most acute and thorny global issue. In order to avert a war on the Korean peninsula it is necessary to terminate the DPRK-U.S. relations of confrontation and opt for improving them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For the U.S. to drop its hostile policy to stifle the DPRK is the master key to terminating those ties, easing the tensions on the peninsula and averting the war there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the essence of the U.S. hostile policy towards the DPRK to topple down the socialist system of Korean style and establish the political system and order of the American style "free world" in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bilateral relations will reach the phase of more acute confrontation should the U.S. take issue with and work hard to destroy the system in the DPRK as it does now. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The escalated moves of the U.S. to invade the DPRK would only reinforce the faith and will of its army and people to further increase its military muscle to protect the country. The U.S. had better drop its attempt to invade the DPRK before faulting its measures to bolster its defence capability. The DPRK will not level its gun at the U.S. if it does not aim its gun at Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. sanctions and blockade against the DPRK should be lifted to terminate the hostile ties between the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. sanctions and blockade against the DPRK have lasted for more than half a century. But never before has the U.S. pursued such a desperate strategy to isolate and stifle the DPRK through international sanctions and blockade backed by military force as now, while openly manoeuvring to lay an "international siege" to it. This indicates that the U.S. imperialists' start of the second Korean war is becoming a reality. That was why the DPRK government clearly stated that it would consider the U.S. formation of an "international siege" and sanctions and blockade against it as military provocations and acts of aggression against it and strongly react against them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. will have nothing to "concern" about the DPRK and worry about its "security" if it drops its hostile policy to stifle the DPRK and opts for normalizing its relations with Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. had better make a switchover in its policy towards the DPRK, though belatedly, properly understanding the do-or die spirit, persevering will and invincible might of the army and people of the DPRK. This would be in line with the trend of the times towards independence, peace, reconciliation and cooperation and helpful to improving the prestige and image of the U.S. The DPRK will closely follow the U.S. move to make a switchover in its policy towards the DPRK and react to it.

All Koreans Called upon to Place Nation above Anything Else
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 24 (KCNA) -- It is necessary to fully realize national cooperation with the stand and will to place the nation above anything else and rely on its strength in order to advance the movement for reunification under the banner of the Korean nation-first spirit, says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article.
 The article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the achievements made in the inter-Korean relations and the movement for national reunification by the concerted efforts of the Korean nation after the publication of the historic June 15 joint declaration clearly prove that "By our nation itself" is the best and there is nothing impossible for the Koreans if they cooperate with each other. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is necessary to place the nation above anything else and strengthen the national unity in reliance upon its strength, not depending on outside forces and "cooperating" with them. The United States is the biggest trouble-maker for the Koreans who are conducting the movement for reconciliation, cooperation and independent reunification by the concerted efforts of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the Koreans should firmly unite and struggle to resolutely frustrate the U.S. moves to stifle the DPRK and ignite a new war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The more desperately the U.S. works to block the national unity and the reunification movement, the more dynamically all the Koreans should conduct the movement for reconciliation, cooperation and independent reunification under the banner of the June 15 joint declaration, the banner of the Korean nation-first spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They should deal a heavy blow at the sycophantic and traitorous forces depending on outside forces and "cooperating' with them while turning their back on the nation and its driving force. All the fellow countrymen should watch with vigilance the moves of those forces and wage a dynamic struggle to decisively foil them.

Support to Koreans Expressed in Russia
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 24 (KCNA) -- Though the present international situation is complicated and the situation surrounding the Korean peninsula is still tense, support of Russians to the Korean people is consistent, said Yeliseyev, head of the Song and Dance Ensemble of the Russian Ministry of Interior, on Jan. 12.
 He noted that after reading the joint New Year editorial of the DPRK, he came to know better the strength and validity of the Songun politics pursued by leader Kim Jong Il and is deeply sympathetic to it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I, as a soldier, believe that the Korean people, true to the Songun politics, will successfully carry out the tasks laid down in the joint editorial. I and members of the ensemble invariably respect and revere Kim Jong Il and make all possible efforts to support the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A future performance of our ensemble in the DPRK will be one for support to the Korean people advancing under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il.

Appeal of Joint Meeting Supported
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tokyo, January 22 (KNS-KCNA) -- All officials of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and compatriots will vigorously turn out in the sacred movement for national reunification to implement the June 15 joint declaration this year in response to the joint appeal to the Korean nation "Let us pave a wide avenue for independent reunification through national cooperation under the banner of our nation-first spirit!".
 Nam Sung U, vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee of Chongryon, said this in a press statement on Jan. 21. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The appeal of a joint meeting of the DPRK government, political parties and organizations is a just patriotic step reflecting the requirements of the present situation and the ardent desire and will of Koreans in Japan for independent reunification, he said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The United States is rendering the situation of the Korean peninsula extremely strained by shipping sophisticated high-tech military equipment into south Korea and instigating its followers at home and abroad to put a brake on the progress of inter-Korean relations. The only way of saving the destiny of the nation is for all the Koreans in the north, the south and overseas to turn out in the nationwide struggle to foil the U.S. new war provocation moves through national cooperation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the Chongryon officials and compatriots will energetically wage the reunification movement, true to the Songun politics, patriotic one which guarantees the dignity of the nation, national cooperation, peace and independent reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He ardently called on the members of the "South Korean Residents Association in Japan", fellow countrymen with the same blood who have also inherited the proud history and tradition of the nation and long for reunification, to join in the nationwide movement for independent reunification with the stand of national cooperation in the idea of "By our nation itself", together with the compatriots in the north, the south and overseas.

Vice-Chairman of NDFSK Calls for Reunification Movement
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 24 (KCNA) -- The vice-chairman of the Central Committee of the National Democratic Front of South Korea (NDFSK) on Jan. 21 released a press statement supporting the appeal to the seventy million Koreans adopted at the joint meeting of the DPRK government, political parties and organizations, according to the Kugukjonson Internet site.
 The five-point appeal, which calls for demonstrating national dignity, realizing national cooperation, waging anti-U.S. patriotic struggle, implementing the June 15 joint declaration and supporting the Songun politics, is a patriotic measure that can be taken only in Pyongyang, sacred capital of national dignity, the statement noted, pointing out that the NDFSK Central Committee fully supports the appeal, considering it as co-ordinates for national reunification reflecting the unanimous will of all the Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our people will clear away illusion about the United States, chieftain of evil, and wage a vigorous struggle to regain the dignity of the nation with the firm self-confidence that if the seventy million fellow countrymen whose independent spirit and wisdom are best pool efforts and wisdom in response to the appeal, there will be nothing for them to fear and fail to do. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our people will wage a more dynamic campaign for implementing the June 15 joint declaration, a milestone for national reunification in the 21st century, and concentrate all their efforts on dissolving the south Korean "Grand National Party", vicious anti-reunification and anti-June 15 forces, and thus blow up the bulwark of the anti-reunification conservative elements. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our people, members of the blessed nation who are living in peace under the protection of the Songun politics pursued by leader Kim Jong Il, the savior of the destiny of the nation and lodestar of national reunification, will support and defend the Songun politics, all-powerful treasured sword for the Korean nation, in everyway.

Ryu Mi Yong Calls for Taking Lead in National Cooperation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 24 (KCNA) -- Ryu Mi Yong, chairperson of the Central Committee of the Chondoist Chongu Party, in a statement on Jan 23 said that the Chondoists who are proud of patriotic tradition against foreign forces and aggression in the idea of "rejection of West and Japan" and "promotion of national interests and welfare of the people" will take the lead in national cooperation for anti-war, peace and reunification.
 She positively supported and approved the appeal of the joint meeting of the DPRK government, political parties and organizations to the 70 million fellow countrymen, saying that it earnestly reflects the desire of all the fellow countrymen and the idea of Chondoism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that cooperation between the north and the south and remarkable events are the fruition of "By our nation itself", the basic spirit of the June 15 joint declaration, she stressed now is the time for all the fellow countrymen to come out as one to open a new phase for independent reunification through national cooperation under the uplifted banner of our nation-first spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The authorities and figures of political parties and organizations in the north and the south should actively turn out in realizing national cooperation for peace and reunification, she said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She called upon the Chondoists and all the religionists in south Korea to take practical actions to build the structure of the Korean nation's confrontation with the United States at any cost this year, hold nationwide gatherings on holidays and anniversaries common to the nation to share mind and keep pace with each other under the uplifted banner of our nation-first spirit.
